population_description: Individuals under the age of 18 years
Individuals who have recently given birth
Individuals who are currently in labor (also called childbirth)

Individuals who were assigned female at birth. Note that literature reporting in this area may be inconsistent in their reporting of sex vs. gender identity. For the purpose of these analyses, we intend for sex to correspond to the sex assigned at birth, independent of an individual's gender identity.

Individuals who were assigned male at birth. Note that literature reporting in this area may be inconsistent in their reporting of sex vs. gender identity. For the purpose of these analyses, we intend for sex to correspond to the sex assigned at birth, independent of an individual's gender identity.

Individuals for whom a sex was not known at the time of data analysis and reporting. Note that literature reporting in this area may be inconsistent in their reporting of sex vs. gender identity. For the purpose of these analyses, we intend for sex to correspond to the sex assigned at birth, independent of an individual's gender identity.

Individuals of a race/ethnicity other than Asian, Black or African American, Native American, Pacific Islander, or White
Individuals for whom a race was not known at the time of data analysis and reporting

Individuals recruited or presenting at a primary care clinic or other primary care setting
Individuals recruited or presenting at am ophthalmology clinic or other ophthalmology-specific setting
